1
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:14,041
-[YOTSUBA] Uesugi!
-Huh?

2
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:15,250
-What's up?
-Aah!

3
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:17,208
-[giggles]
-Whoa! Yotsuba!

4
00:00:17,291 --> 00:00:18,958
Tomorrow's the big day!

5
00:00:19,041 --> 00:00:20,958
-For what?
-Come on!

6
00:00:21,041 --> 00:00:22,708
You know what day
I'm talking about!

7
00:00:22,791 --> 00:00:24,875
See, look!
[giggles]

8
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:26,666
It's the school camping trip!

9
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:29,166
Have you read
the information booklet?

10
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:30,583
Can't say that I have.

11
00:00:30,666 --> 00:00:33,083
They've got all kinds
of fun activities!

12
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:37,125
Outdoor cooking and skiing,
fishing, hiking, of course.

13
00:00:37,208 --> 00:00:40,333
And then, there's the campfire!

14
00:00:40,416 --> 00:00:42,791
Where the dance happens!

15
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:45,416
Rumor is, whoever's paired up
when the music stops

16
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,500
will be destined to spend the
rest of their lives together!

17
00:00:49,583 --> 00:00:51,833
I heard that a lot of people
have ended up dating

18
00:00:51,916 --> 00:00:54,208
because of it,
so the legend's gotta be legit!

19
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:56,375
Like I said,
students shouldn't date.

20
00:00:56,458 --> 00:00:57,708
It's just a waste of your time.

21
00:00:57,791 --> 00:00:58,875
Aw. That's sad!

22
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:00,750
If you had feelings
for somebody,

23
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,416
you would want to go out
with them, right?

24
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:03,625
Wouldn't you, Miku?

25
00:01:04,666 --> 00:01:05,583
-Miku?
-Hmm?

26
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:09,791
Wait, why do we date people
we like, anyway?

27
00:01:09,875 --> 00:01:11,500
-Huh?
-Huh?

28
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:12,833
[ICHIKA]
That's easy.

29
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:14,666
When you like somebody,

30
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:17,375
you want nothing more
than to be with them.

31
00:01:17,458 --> 00:01:20,083
Miku should know
that feeling pretty well.

32
00:01:20,166 --> 00:01:22,083
No. I don't.

33
00:01:22,166 --> 00:01:24,458
All right.
Enough foolishness.

34
00:01:24,541 --> 00:01:25,875
It's time to start studying!

35
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:27,583
Again? I'm not ready!

36
00:01:27,666 --> 00:01:30,166
I have a shoot,
so I'll have to skip out.

37
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:32,333
Sorry. I sent you
a text earlier.

38
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:33,416
Huh?

39
00:01:35,416 --> 00:01:38,625
Yeah, and I'd better
get set for tomorrow.

40
00:01:38,708 --> 00:01:40,416
-[giggling]
-Hey, you can't just take off!

41
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,333
-Should have known.
-[ICHIKA] Miku.

42
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:46,458
My class has a meeting
about the camping trip later on.

43
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,333
Do the usual, please?

44
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:50,916
[MIKU]
Okay.

45
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,708
♪

46
00:01:57,291 --> 00:01:58,833
[FUTARO]
The usual?

47
00:01:58,916 --> 00:02:01,625
What kind of shady operation
are they up to?

48
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:06,958
Ichika? But I thought
she just left for work.

49
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,750
[gasps]
It can't be!

50
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:15,291
Is that Miku?
It's uncanny!

51
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:48,708
Oh, good.
You made it.

52
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:50,458
Thanks, I appreciate it.

53
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:51,666
[MIKU]
Sure.

54
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:54,000
You're Maeda, right?

55
00:03:54,083 --> 00:03:55,833
Where is everybody?

56
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,333
Um...

57
00:03:57,416 --> 00:04:00,041
Actually, there's no meeting.
I lied to you.

58
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:01,500
What?

59
00:04:01,583 --> 00:04:03,500
Look. If you'll have me,

60
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:05,833
I'd really like to dance
with you at the campfire.

61
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,750
[MIKU]
With me? Why?

62
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:13,000
Uh, well, you know.

63
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:15,083
I... I really like you.

64
00:04:17,708 --> 00:04:19,291
[MIKU]
Didn't expect that.

65
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:22,416
But Ichika's cute, so she
probably gets this all the time.

66
00:04:23,416 --> 00:04:26,250
Thanks for that. I'll get back
to you later, okay? Bye.

67
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,041
I need an answer now.

68
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:30,583
Don't leave me hanging, Nakano.

69
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,041
[FUTARO] If you lie,
it comes back to haunt you.

70
00:04:32,125 --> 00:04:33,958
-[MIKU] Um...
-[FUTARO] Oh well,

71
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:35,500
you reap what you sow.

72
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:36,875
[MAEDA]
Hang on.

73
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:38,791
Something's a little different
about you today.

74
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:43,375
-I think it's your hair.
-Really?

75
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:46,208
You're a quintuplet,
right, Nakano?

76
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,750
You and your sisters
all look alike.

77
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,083
You tryin' to pull
a fast one on me?

78
00:04:55,875 --> 00:04:58,250
There you are. I've been
looking for you, Ichika.

79
00:04:59,416 --> 00:05:01,666
Your sisters want
to talk to you.

80
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:03,083
You should go find them.

81
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:05,041
Futaro, I...

82
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,500
Now listen here, buddy,

83
00:05:06,583 --> 00:05:08,583
this is between me
and Nakano, not you.

84
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:10,708
And I don't know what makes
you think you can call her

85
00:05:10,791 --> 00:05:12,583
by her first name
like that, but don't!

86
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,750
Give her some time
to consider!

87
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,958
Think about someone
else's feelings for once!

88
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:21,125
[MIKU] That's not very
convincing coming from him.

89
00:05:21,208 --> 00:05:23,916
This is none of your
frickin' business!

90
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,208
Quit being nosy and leave!

91
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:27,416
Actually, it is my business.

92
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,750
-Stop it.
-Oh yeah?

93
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,250
That's it.

94
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,916
[MIKU]
Please calm down!

95
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,250
[MAEDA]
Get lost, punk!

96
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:41,458
Sorry. I promised Futaro
I would dance with him!

97
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,500
-Huh?
-Huh?

98
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:47,208
-Hold on. I mean--
-Yeah, right!

99
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:49,666
That's a lie. You're way
out of this nerd's league!

100
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,916
No! That isn't true at all!

101
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,541
Futaro is, uh, um...

102
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,958
really cool.

103
00:05:58,041 --> 00:06:00,458
[MAEDA]
What? Are you guys dating?

104
00:06:00,541 --> 00:06:02,666
Yeah! We're such lovebirds!

105
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:04,500
Come on,
let's walk home together!

106
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,916
Uh, sure.
We'll go with that.

107
00:06:08,875 --> 00:06:11,625
Hold it!
If you really are a couple,

108
00:06:11,708 --> 00:06:14,000
shouldn't you at least
hold each other's hands?

109
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:15,916
What's wrong?
You can't do it?

110
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,208
That's kinda suspicious.

111
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:19,625
No, it's not.

112
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:21,250
It's not like every couple
does things

113
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:23,083
exactly the same wa--

114
00:06:25,916 --> 00:06:27,541
Mi-- Ichika!

115
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,958
Um, listen.

116
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:32,708
I'm not blushing 'cause I'm
holding hands with my boyfriend.

117
00:06:32,791 --> 00:06:36,416
You know, because we totally
do this all the time.

118
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:39,125
Damn it!
All right, fine, I believe you.

119
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,875
Maeda? This is probably
a bad time to ask,

120
00:06:43,958 --> 00:06:47,041
but what made you want to
confess something so personal?

121
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:49,500
You're really twisting
the knife.

122
00:06:49,583 --> 00:06:50,458
[MIKU]
Sorry.

123
00:06:51,791 --> 00:06:53,875
Um, well, I guess,

124
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:56,875
you do it because you want
that person all to yourself.

125
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:58,041
Or somethin'.

126
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:01,125
[MIKU]
Oh.

127
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:02,875
You want them all to yourself.

128
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:05,416
Ugh. What the hell am I sayin'?

129
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,375
Look! Don't you give
Nakano trouble!

130
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:10,083
Trust me, most of the time,

131
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:11,958
it's Nakano giving me
the trouble.

132
00:07:12,041 --> 00:07:13,791
Aw, you're so silly!

133
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,083
Let's head home, Futaro.

134
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:18,125
[whispers] You don't have
to cling so tight.

135
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:22,208
This is what Ichika would do.
That means I have to do it.

136
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:24,041
Don't worry, it's fine.

137
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:28,458
Anyway, you said no.

138
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,500
You sure that was okay?

139
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:33,416
Of course. Ichika's putting
work first right now.

140
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:36,625
I know, but what about
the whole campfire dance thing?

141
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,833
[YOTSUBA]
Hey, there you guys are!

142
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:44,125
Well, clock's ticking!

143
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:45,625
Huh?

144
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:47,458
[YOTSUBA] We're going
to pick out some new outfits

145
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:49,750
for you to wear
on the camping trip!

146
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,500
Here's what I picked out.

147
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:53,750
It's loud with lots of color!

148
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:57,041
I honestly can't tell
whether you're messing with me.

149
00:07:57,125 --> 00:08:00,250
Traditional style.
That's what suits you best.

150
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:02,416
Don't you think
this is too traditional?

151
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,708
I decided I would
pick something

152
00:08:03,791 --> 00:08:05,750
that makes you look
a bit manlier.

153
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:07,833
And this is your idea
of manliness?

154
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:12,291
Nino's thinking hard!
She's focused!

155
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:14,833
Why are none of you
taking this seriously?

156
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:19,541
Um, are you sure?
The cost.

157
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:21,708
We didn't buy that
for your sake.

158
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:23,458
We just couldn't be seen
in public with you

159
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:25,000
looking like a hobo.

160
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:27,625
You know, the way we're going
out on the town with you

161
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,000
and helping you pick out
all these new outfits and stuff,

162
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:33,041
it's almost like
we're on a date, huh?

163
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:36,750
This is just
a normal shopping trip.

164
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:39,333
It's a waste of time
for high schoolers to date.

165
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:40,750
You know that.

166
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,166
Oh wow!

167
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:44,250
When you say that,
you sound just like Uesugi!

168
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:46,000
Hey, don't lump me in
with that jerk!

169
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:49,041
The two of us are nothing more
than a student and her teacher!

170
00:08:49,125 --> 00:08:51,250
So we need to maintain
some distance!

171
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,125
[FUTARO]
That's exactly what we're doing!

172
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:55,500
[YOTSUBA]
Bye, Uesugi!

173
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:58,916
Make sure you read
through that booklet carefully!

174
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,541
That's not happening!

175
00:09:00,625 --> 00:09:02,375
[YOTSUBA] You better
show up in the morning!

176
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:06,000
Let's make some
great memories together!

177
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,250
Uh. That's right.

178
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:11,958
My phone.

179
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:14,625
Uh-oh.

180
00:09:16,666 --> 00:09:19,375
[FUTARO panting]

181
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:22,291
Raiha! Are you okay?

182
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:24,541
Big Brother.

183
00:09:24,625 --> 00:09:26,458
I think I might have a fever.

184
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,250
I didn't mean to bother you.

185
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,750
-Sorry.
-No, it's okay.

186
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:33,208
You've always been
on the frail side,

187
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:34,750
so I totally understand.

188
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:36,041
But I'm here now.

189
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:37,458
And I brought home
some drinks and medicine

190
00:09:37,541 --> 00:09:38,791
to help you feel better, too.

191
00:09:38,875 --> 00:09:41,333
Thank you.
Can I have the medicine now?

192
00:09:41,416 --> 00:09:43,416
-Sure thing.
-Bring me a towel?

193
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,666
-Yup!
-Do my homework for me?

194
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:49,125
Mm-hmm! Wait, are you trying
to get me to spoil you?

195
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,250
[RAIHA]
Thanks a lot.

196
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:55,458
Dad says he'll be home from work
as quickly as he can.

197
00:09:55,541 --> 00:09:56,541
Okay.

198
00:09:58,208 --> 00:10:01,041
Anyway, you have a
school trip tomorrow, don't you?

199
00:10:02,041 --> 00:10:03,166
Uh-huh.

200
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,416
Then could I ask you
one last favor?

201
00:10:06,416 --> 00:10:07,916
I want to hear
lots of fun stories

202
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,375
when you get back home, okay?

203
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:12,291
I'll be all right
on my own until then.

204
00:10:12,375 --> 00:10:15,916
♪

205
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:18,375
Yeah, you got it.

206
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:20,375
-Now rest up.
-Mm-hmm.

207
00:10:20,458 --> 00:10:22,250
♪

208
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:25,958
[FEMALE TEACHER]
Okay, everyone...

209
00:10:26,041 --> 00:10:27,625
[MALE TEACHER]
Itsuki Nakano, a word please?

210
00:10:27,708 --> 00:10:29,166
Uh, Sir?

211
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:30,583
We've had a last-minute change.

212
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:31,916
Would you mind
taking over planning

213
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,458
for the test of courage?

214
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:34,666
Huh?

215
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:36,916
-[panting]
-[door opens]

216
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,375
Raiha! Are you okay?

217
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:41,666
Futaro?

218
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:46,291
Hey, Dad. She's still asleep.
Keep it down, please.

219
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:47,875
[snoring softly]

220
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:50,125
[ISANARI] So you've been
taking care of her?

221
00:10:50,208 --> 00:10:51,708
Wait.

222
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:53,750
The bus for your school trip
must be long gone by now!

223
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:54,791
You think so?

224
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:56,833
I didn't care enough to check.

225
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:59,000
But, hey,
I guess this means I can study

226
00:10:59,083 --> 00:11:01,125
to my heart's content
for the next three days.

227
00:11:03,583 --> 00:11:05,583
[ISANARI] Futaro,
you forgot something.

228
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,875
Sorry, I couldn't
get home before now.

229
00:11:10,791 --> 00:11:12,458
You only get to do this once.

230
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:17,125
You could still make it,
if you actually tried to.

231
00:11:17,208 --> 00:11:20,166
The bus is gone.
I really don't care.

232
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:24,916
-Gosh, I sure am hungry!
-[FUTARO/ISANARI] Huh?

233
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,458
Your fever. Is it gone?

234
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:28,666
Yup, all gone!

235
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:30,791
Thanks for all your help.

236
00:11:30,875 --> 00:11:32,875
I feel way better
all of a sudden.

237
00:11:32,958 --> 00:11:34,416
You should go on your trip.

238
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,083
Nah, I missed the bus.

239
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:38,458
[ITSUKI] Sure did.
It left a little while ago.

240
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:42,000
[FUTARO]
Whoa, why are you here?

241
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:43,458
I'm solving a problem.

242
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:47,375
[FUTARO]
Hey, stop it!

243
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:50,458
Sorry. I need
to borrow Uesugi.

244
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:52,416
-Okay.
-Okay.

245
00:11:53,458 --> 00:11:55,958
Hang on.
What are you...

246
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:58,375
[gasps

247
00:11:58,458 --> 00:12:00,333
♪

248
00:12:00,416 --> 00:12:01,875
I don't understand.

249
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:04,458
-Hey, Futaro.
-You're late.

250
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:06,000
Are you ready to go?

251
00:12:06,083 --> 00:12:07,875
It sure took you long enough.

252
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:10,458
They wanted me
to take over for you,

253
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:12,041
but I wasn't having that.

254
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,666
I'm terrified of ghosts.

255
00:12:15,125 --> 00:12:16,583
So you're gonna have to do it.

256
00:12:16,666 --> 00:12:18,958
♪

257
00:12:19,041 --> 00:12:20,333
If you say so.

258
00:12:21,791 --> 00:12:24,000
I guess I'll come too.

259
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:26,916
Okay, guys! Road trip!

260
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,875
♪

261
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:33,166
[QUINTUPLETS]
Quintuplet Game time!

262
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:34,791
In this game,
we assign each of us

263
00:12:34,875 --> 00:12:36,000
a finger on a person's hand,

264
00:12:36,083 --> 00:12:37,458
and then we try to guess
which one of us

265
00:12:37,541 --> 00:12:39,250
is the finger hiding
behind the other hand.

266
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:41,291
Doesn't that sound fun?

267
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:42,916
Okay, who am I?

268
00:12:44,041 --> 00:12:46,000
-Nino.
-Nah, Miku.

269
00:12:46,083 --> 00:12:48,208
-It's me!
-Nino, for sure.

270
00:12:50,416 --> 00:12:51,708
No way, back off!

271
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:54,000
Touching is against the rules,
you big cheater!

272
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:56,333
It's Nino.

273
00:12:56,416 --> 00:12:58,875
Sorry, it's Miku.

274
00:12:58,958 --> 00:13:01,125
[FUTARO]
I should've guessed that.

275
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:03,208
Fine. My turn. Let's go.

276
00:13:03,291 --> 00:13:04,875
Someone's energetic today.

277
00:13:04,958 --> 00:13:06,916
'Cause I haven't traveled
in years!

278
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,916
Not since elementary school!

279
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,666
So I feel like I'm unstoppable!

280
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:12,958
Makes sense.

281
00:13:13,041 --> 00:13:14,916
Except we've been stopped
by this traffic

282
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,458
for over an hour now.

283
00:13:16,541 --> 00:13:18,375
[wind whistling]

284
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:24,166
[FUTARO]
Wow, this room is amazing!

285
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:26,375
[ITSUKI] It only sleeps
four people, though.

286
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:28,416
You're crazy if you think
I'm about to share

287
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,000
a room with this guy!

288
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:32,916
They had another big group
show up at the last minute,

289
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,250
so there wasn't
anything else available.

290
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:37,000
Then let's find another place.

291
00:13:37,083 --> 00:13:39,041
[YOTSUBA]
We can't, the driver went home.

292
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:40,583
Wait, I know!

293
00:13:40,666 --> 00:13:42,791
He can sleep in that extra room
I saw around the front!

294
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:44,291
[wind whistling]

295
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:46,416
What?
He would freeze overnight!

296
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:48,250
Oh, come on, he'd live.

297
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:49,916
-I don't think so.
-Huh? What's this?

298
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,458
[ITSUKI]
Only one way to find out, right?

299
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:55,250
I made you a good luck charm
to keep you safe

300
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:56,708
while you travel.

301
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:59,125
I hope you have a good time
at your school camp.

302
00:13:59,208 --> 00:14:02,250
P.S! I'm expecting
a gift in return!

303
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,583
-Raiha.
-[chuckles]

304
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:06,041
[NINO]
Just hear me out.

305
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:08,791
[FUTARO]
Yup, I like this place!

306
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:11,791
Let's stop complaining
and have some fun!

307
00:14:11,875 --> 00:14:13,416
That's it, family meeting.

308
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:17,708
[NINO] All five of us need
to be extremely careful.

309
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:20,416
-[YOTSUBA] What for?
-[NINO] Well, you know.

310
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:23,000
We're going to share a room
with a young man tonight.

311
00:14:23,083 --> 00:14:25,833
And teenage boys
are basically animals.

312
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:27,708
[FUTARO]
Rawr!

313
00:14:27,791 --> 00:14:30,125
Come on, he's not
gonna try anything.

314
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,041
-Let's do it.
-[squeals]

315
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:33,958
[ALL gasp]

316
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:35,541
Um, do what?

317
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:39,125
I brought some cards.
Let's play.

318
00:14:39,208 --> 00:14:40,458
Is that all?

319
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:42,500
Oh, that's so old-school.

320
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:43,833
So what should we play?

321
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:45,916
[FUTARO]
How about fan-tan?

322
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,958
[ITSUKI]
It is a valid concern, though.

323
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:51,041
I mean, we are students
and teacher, after all.

324
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,666
[ICHIKA sighs]

325
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:58,416
-That was an intense card game.
-[MIKU] Yeah.

326
00:14:59,708 --> 00:15:00,625
Want one?

327
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:02,833
I'm okay for now.

328
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:07,208
Miku, after what happened,

329
00:15:07,291 --> 00:15:09,166
it looks like
I'll be dancing with him.

330
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:10,958
Are you sure
you're okay with that?

331
00:15:13,166 --> 00:15:16,875
Yeah. I'm the one who messed
everything up, so it's fine.

332
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,333
[ICHIKA]
All right.

333
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:22,208
Well, I'll try
to look after him then.

334
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:23,833
Just leave it
to your oldest sister.

335
00:15:26,041 --> 00:15:27,875
[MIKU]
Keep someone all to myself.

336
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:30,333
I couldn't do that.

337
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:33,958
We're five fifths,
and together we're one.

338
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:36,041
Besides...

339
00:15:37,375 --> 00:15:40,083
if it's Ichika,
then I'm not worried.

340
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,666
[ICHIKA]
Miku says it's okay,

341
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:45,166
so I guess it is.

342
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,916
♪

343
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:53,625
[FUTARO]
A smorgasbord!

344
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,583
I want to box it up and save it!

345
00:15:56,666 --> 00:15:58,166
Please don't do that.

346
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,166
[YOTSUBA] Tomorrow,
we're getting rice curry.

347
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:03,125
It's gonna look pretty sad
after this spread, huh?

348
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:04,708
I don't know if I want
to eat anything

349
00:16:04,791 --> 00:16:06,166
your team's in charge of.

350
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,583
-Shut up.
-Oh, that's right!

351
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:11,375
Come to think of it, I haven't
even looked at the schedule yet.

352
00:16:11,458 --> 00:16:13,333
The main events
for day two are:

353
00:16:13,416 --> 00:16:16,458
orienteering, cooking, and then
the test of courage at night.

354
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:18,750
Day three will have
the optional mountain climb,

355
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:22,166
skiing, fishing, and last
but not least, the campfire.

356
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,375
[ICHIKA] Why do you have
the whole thing memorized?

357
00:16:25,458 --> 00:16:28,333
Oh, yeah!
I got more info on the campfire!

358
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:30,041
If you want the legend
to come true,

359
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:31,583
you should hold hands
at the end!

360
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,625
Not this nonsense again.

361
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:35,125
What legend?

362
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:36,500
[NINO]
Eh, don't worry about it.

363
00:16:36,583 --> 00:16:38,250
None of us have a dance partner,

364
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:40,458
so it's not like
anything'll happen anyway.

365
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:41,708
[ICHIKA/FUTARO/MIKU gasp]

366
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:43,041
[FUTARO]
Right, I forgot.

367
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:45,083
I got roped
into dancing with Ichika.

368
00:16:45,166 --> 00:16:47,625
Not that I believe
in that foolish legend,

369
00:16:47,708 --> 00:16:49,916
but it's an awkward
situation nonetheless.

370
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:53,583
Ugh. I've got tons
of better things to do

371
00:16:53,666 --> 00:16:55,458
than dance around a fire.

372
00:16:55,541 --> 00:16:56,916
[MIKU]
That's convenient,

373
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,875
since I'm pretty certain
you didn't get any offers.

374
00:16:59,958 --> 00:17:01,666
Oh, I get it,
you're just bitter!

375
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:04,041
[NINO]
Huh? Hey, who asked you?

376
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:05,750
Anyway.

377
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,500
They've got
an outdoor bath here.

378
00:17:07,583 --> 00:17:09,083
It looks really nice.

379
00:17:11,125 --> 00:17:12,833
Does that say "mixed"?

380
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:16,833
What? So not only
are we sharing a room,

381
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,291
we have to share
a bath with him too?

382
00:17:18,375 --> 00:17:20,083
That's unacceptable!

383
00:17:20,166 --> 00:17:22,291
We don't all have to use it
at the same time.

384
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:23,708
Come on, Nino.

385
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:25,250
I can't believe
you're too embarrassed

386
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:27,250
to go into the bath with me.

387
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:30,291
It's nothing you and I
haven't done before, right?

388
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:31,791
-You what?
-Wait!

389
00:17:31,875 --> 00:17:33,791
That's not...
Shut up!

390
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:36,041
[FUTARO laughs]
You know you deserved that.

391
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:37,083
[ICHIKA/YOTSUBA laugh]

392
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:42,000
[NINO sighs]
This is great!

393
00:17:42,083 --> 00:17:44,750
[ICHIKA sighs]
It's not a mixed bath.

394
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,750
I guess I misread it.

395
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:49,208
We don't really take baths
together anymore, do we?

396
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:50,541
It's been a few years now.

397
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:54,916
Is it just me or have
your boobs gotten bigger?

398
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,250
No, we're all the same size.

399
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:58,666
[NINO]
By the way,

400
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:01,083
something seems off
about you-know-who today.

401
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:02,875
Oh, I wouldn't worry,
it's probably

402
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:04,833
'cause he doesn't go
on trips very often.

403
00:18:04,916 --> 00:18:06,916
He's just tired
from studying all night.

404
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,041
It's no big deal.

405
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:10,416
Even so,
people tend to get flirty

406
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,458
when they're on
a traveler's high like that.

407
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:14,541
My concern is that
there's barely enough space

408
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:17,500
in that tiny room of ours
to lay down six futons.

409
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:19,500
So which one of us
will be sleeping next to him?

410
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:21,333
-[FUTARO] Rawr!
-[wolf howling]

411
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:24,833
Nino, come on.
You're overthinking this.

412
00:18:24,916 --> 00:18:27,375
Futaro's our friend,
he wouldn't make a move on us.

413
00:18:28,416 --> 00:18:31,333
She's right! Uesugi's not
interested in us like that!

414
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:34,333
I assume you're okay
with sleeping next to him, then?

415
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:35,958
[YOTSUBA]
Huh?

416
00:18:36,041 --> 00:18:38,125
You seem pretty confident
things'll just stay friendly.

417
00:18:38,208 --> 00:18:39,958
So you do it.

418
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:42,125
Well, on second thought...

419
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:43,583
I'm not that sure.

420
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:47,000
Let's see.
Maybe you'd be the best choice.

421
00:18:47,083 --> 00:18:50,291
Hold on!
What makes you say that?

422
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:52,166
[ITSUKI] I don't know,
because if he came onto you,

423
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:53,541
you'd be the one to punch him?

424
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:58,208
[NINO] Ichika! You haven't said
anything, you do it!

425
00:18:58,291 --> 00:18:59,833
I don't see why.

426
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:03,083
[NINO]
You're just friends, aren't you?

427
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:05,875
[ICHIKA]
Yeah.

428
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:09,041
You could say
that Futaro's a friend.

429
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:11,458
Then it should be you.

430
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,666
[MIKU]
Wait. I know.

431
00:19:15,250 --> 00:19:17,666
Trust me. This way is fair.

432
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:22,125
[NINO]
I see. That's a good idea.

433
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:23,833
If nobody wants to.

434
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:25,625
Then everybody has to.

435
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:27,958
That's the only
reasonable solution.

436
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:30,916
Plus, he won't start something
if we're all there.

437
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,958
And if he can't tell who's who.

438
00:19:33,041 --> 00:19:36,333
Well, apparently all that takes
is wearing our hair down.

439
00:19:36,416 --> 00:19:37,833
This is foolproof!

440
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:41,666
♪

441
00:19:48,916 --> 00:19:50,666
He's out cold.

442
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:53,208
We should all get some shuteye.

443
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:55,000
-[ITSUKI] Yeah.
-[ICHIKA] Sounds good.

444
00:19:56,125 --> 00:19:59,833
[birds chirping]

445
00:20:06,083 --> 00:20:07,125
[gasps]

446
00:20:12,458 --> 00:20:15,541
How'd I get here?
This is so weird.

447
00:20:15,625 --> 00:20:18,208
Oh.
[chuckles]

448
00:20:18,291 --> 00:20:20,333
Guess we moved during the night.

449
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:26,000
This is the second time
I've seen him sleep.

450
00:20:26,083 --> 00:20:29,125
If this gets my heart racing,
then we're not just friends.

451
00:20:30,875 --> 00:20:32,333
Or just partners.

452
00:20:37,375 --> 00:20:38,875
But that's okay, right?

453
00:20:40,166 --> 00:20:41,916
Rise and shine, everyone!

454
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,083
It's time for, uh...

455
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:45,458
Uh...

456
00:20:47,083 --> 00:20:48,583
[gasps]

457
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:49,958
[door closes]

458
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:51,083
[gasps]

459
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:54,583
[breathing heavily]

460
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:56,125
[ITSUKI]
No way.

461
00:20:56,208 --> 00:20:57,458
Were they...

462
00:20:57,541 --> 00:20:59,083
-[MALE TEACHER] Nakano?
-Huh?

463
00:20:59,166 --> 00:21:00,833
I thought that was you!

464
00:21:00,916 --> 00:21:02,583
How did you end up
staying at this inn?

465
00:21:02,666 --> 00:21:04,666
♪

466
00:21:06,458 --> 00:21:08,583
[FUTARO] What are the odds
we'd get snowed in and wind up

467
00:21:08,666 --> 00:21:10,916
staying at the same place
as they were?

468
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,000
[STUDENTS chattering]

469
00:21:12,083 --> 00:21:14,333
Can't believe we never saw them.

470
00:21:14,416 --> 00:21:16,500
-Hey, what's with you?
-Huh? Nothing!

471
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:20,875
I didn't get a good enough look
to be sure what happened.

472
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:22,958
But one of us
was definitely super close

473
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:24,500
to Uesugi this morning.

474
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:28,458
♪

475
00:21:28,541 --> 00:21:29,666
Listen, Ichika.

476
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,750
If you're serious
about your career,

477
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,166
you should think
about taking a break

478
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:34,791
from high school for a while.

479
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:37,541
♪

480
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:39,458
[GIRL 1] Have you picked someone
to dance with

481
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:40,833
at the campfire?

482
00:21:40,916 --> 00:21:42,125
No, not exactly.

483
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:45,333
You've got
some high standards, don't you?

484
00:21:45,416 --> 00:21:46,458
I guess so.

485
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:52,166
♪

486
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:55,125
[NINO] If only I could meet
somebody like him.

487
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:58,375
Oh, hey. You know what
the campfire legend is, right?

488
00:21:58,458 --> 00:22:01,166
[GIRL 2] Of course!
It brings couples together!

489
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:03,458
[GIRL 1]
And I hear it's forever, too!

490
00:22:05,041 --> 00:22:06,458
[YOTSUBA]
Just wait, Uesugi.

491
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:08,375
I swear you're gonna have fun!

492
00:22:08,458 --> 00:22:10,958
I'll make sure this trip
is one you never forget!

493
00:22:12,166 --> 00:22:14,000
[ITSUKI] We're a teacher
and his students.

494
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,666
Even if a student
develops feelings,

495
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:19,208
it's the
teacher's responsibility

496
00:22:19,291 --> 00:22:20,916
to set things right again.

497
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,625
Uesugi, it's decided.

498
00:22:23,708 --> 00:22:26,208
I'm treating this camping trip
as an opportunity to figure out

499
00:22:26,291 --> 00:22:28,083
whether or not you're really
up to the challenge

500
00:22:28,166 --> 00:22:29,958
of being our tutor.

501
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,125
[QUINTUPLETS]
Quintuplet Trivia!

502
00:24:02,208 --> 00:24:04,250
[ITSUKI] You're so good
at impersonating us, Miku.

503
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:05,875
[ICHIKA] Let's see your
